	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=83710><span id=Scholar>jcasetnl</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>153 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Hello All - <br><br>I finally got my level 22 spells.&nbsp;&nbsp;Root is a lot of fun, and combined with Ward is a great way to work over undead for good exp.  <br><br>But I was wondering how useful archery would be against non-undead mobs, mainly because the skill maxes at 75.  This is the equivalent of about level 15 or so.  So if I root a level 25 mob and then try to peck at it with arrows, am I just wasting my time?  I'd like to know before I try to get my archery skill maxed.<br><br>Thanks</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
